-- Investcorp says buys U.S. real estate assets for around $250 mln
-- By David French
-- Tue Sep 16, 2014 02:18AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, Sept 16 (Reuters) - Investcorp, an alternative investment manager based in Bahrain, said on Tuesday it had acquired a portfolio of office and industrial property assets in three cities in the United States for around $250 million.

The purchases, done in separate transactions, were completed by the firm's U.S.-based real estate arm, a statement from Investcorp said.